{"tid":854045,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"馬凱被拒續簽證　歐盟：立「令人憂心」先例　損香港國際地位和信譽","createTime":"2018-10-09T05:30:20.000Z","updateTime":"2018-10-09T06:00:23.000Z","uid":39464,"like":20,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":13,"replies":[{"pid":"0adba8fceec46c0b61be35c432bf1b252f92485f","tid":854045,"uid":39464,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-09T05:30:20.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://cdn.thestandnews.com/media/photos/cache/fcc_7wYsB_1200x0.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thestandnews.com%2Fmedia%2Fphotos%2Fcache%2Ffcc_7wYsB_1200x0.png&h=cadd60ea&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n香港外國記者會（FCC）第一副主席、英國《金融時報》亞洲新聞主編馬凱（Victor Mallet）工作簽證續期被拒，事件繼續引起國際關注。<br />\n<br />\n歐盟昨日（8日）發表聲明，指香港政府拒絕為馬凱工作簽證續期，立下了「令人憂心」的先例，政府在沒有另行作出「令人可信」（credible）的解釋之下，此決定明顯是有政治動機， 令外界深切關注香港的新聞和言論自由。今次事件，可能破壞香港在「一國兩制」下的國際地位和信譽。<br />\n<br />\n歐盟強調，新聞工作者必須能夠獨立工作，不受任何干預。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.thestandnews.com/politics/馬凱被拒續簽證-歐盟-立-令人憂心-先例-損香港國際地位和信譽/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestandnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F%E9%A6%AC%E5%87%B1%E8%A2%AB%E6%8B%92%E7%BA%8C%E7%B0%BD%E8%AD%89-%E6%AD%90%E7%9B%9F-%E7%AB%8B-%E4%BB%A4%E4%BA%BA%E6%86%82%E5%BF%83-%E5%85%88%E4%BE%8B-%E6%90%8D%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B%E5%9C%B0%E4%BD%8D%E5%92%8C%E4%BF%A1%E8%AD%BD%2F&d=tpWi1nmtpTniQiL6rb93DuPnIAwyWqphGIcg0J4V%2Buw%3D&h=bdcbcdf8\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestandnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F%E9%A6%AC%E5%87%B1%E8%A2%AB%E6%8B%92%E7%BA%8C%E7%B0%BD%E8%AD%89-%E6%AD%90%E7%9B%9F-%E7%AB%8B-%E4%BB%A4%E4%BA%BA%E6%86%82%E5%BF%83-%E5%85%88%E4%BE%8B-%E6%90%8D%E9%A6%99%E6%B8%AF%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B%E5%9C%B0%E4%BD%8D%E5%92%8C%E4%BF%A1%E8%AD%BD%2F&h=2cf46c44\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.thestandnews.com/politics/馬凱被拒續簽證-歐盟-立-令人憂心-先例-損香港國際地位和信譽/</a>"},{"pid":"adc428bae78d772294a1ccd5f6783eca8f1babc6","tid":854045,"uid":39464,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-09T05:32:58.000Z","msg":"<strong>Statement by the Spokesperson on the refusal to renew a visa for a foreign journalist in Hong Kong</strong><br />\n<br />\nThe decision by the Hong Kong authorities to refuse to renew the working visa of the Financial Times' Asia news editor, Victor Mallet, sets a worrying precedent. In the absence of a credible alternative explanation from the authorities, <span style=\"color: red;\">the decision appears politically motivated</span> and therefore raises serious concerns about freedom of the press and freedom of expression in Hong Kong. <span style=\"color: red;\">It risks damaging Hong Kong's international standing and trust in the &quot;one country, two systems&quot; principle.</span><br />\n<br />\nJournalists must be allowed to perform their work independently and without interference.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://eeas.europa.eu/delegations/hong-kong/51753/statement-spokesperson-refusal-renew-visa-foreign-journalist-hong-kong_en\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Feeas.europa.eu%2Fdelegations%2Fhong-kong%2F51753%2Fstatement-spokesperson-refusal-renew-visa-foreign-journalist-hong-kong_en&d=tpWi1nmtpTniQiL6rb93DuPnIAwyWqphGIcg0J4V%2Buw%3D&h=0ee132ee\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://eeas.europa.eu/delegations/hong-kong/51753/statement-spokesperson-refusal-renew-visa-foreign-journalist-hong-kong_en</a>"},{"pid":"f9de7f1d24e9d460d3170e7f95346d43e53ee2f7","tid":854045,"uid":108347,"like":11,"dislike":0,"score":11,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-10-09T05:35:02.000Z","msg":"政府真係當而家係同平時同冇得反抗嘅香港人&ldquo;解釋&rdquo;咁樣講嘢<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e86e37f89fe9f527188984bc2e32f50dbaae0625","tid":854045,"uid":25148,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-09T05:36:07.000Z","msg":"同維尼一齊做臭個朵攬住一齊死<br />\n唔好話舐共 你話有路我都信"},{"pid":"faa9203155c53fd99c9